Proposed Amendments to HB 4079 Page 5

1 quirements that the notice:
2 “(A) Must include at least the following information:
3 “(i) The general location of the federal immigration authority; and
4 “(ii) Whether classes or campus operations are affected by the
5 presence of the federal immigration authority.
6 “(B) May not disclose any of the following information:
7 “(i) Personally identifiable information; or
8 “(ii) Other information that may not be legally disclosed.
9 “(C) May not disclose information when the disclosure:
10 “(i) May threaten the health or safety of the students or employees
11 of the institution of higher education; or
12 “(ii) Is prohibited by a court order.
13 “(D) Must be provided as expediently as possible by existing meth-
14 ods used for providing electronic communications.
15 “(f) Ensure compliance with ORS 180.805 and 181A.826 and any pol-
16 icies adopted based on a model policy published as provided by ORS
17 180.810.
18 “(g) Require that annual training is provided to any person identi-
19 fied or designated as provided by paragraph (a) of this subsection. The
20 training must, at a minimum, include:
21 “(A) Information on the requirements of this section and on any
22 applicable model policies published by the Attorney General under ORS
23 180.810.
24 “(B) Initial training, followed by subsequent training at least once
25 every two years.
26 “(h) Require that the policy adopted under this section be made
27 available:
28 “(A) On the websites of the institution of higher education in any
29 languages that are regularly used to communicate effectively with the
30 students of the campus, as determined by the governing board; and
HB 4079-5 2/9/26
Proposed Amendments to HB 4079 Page 6

1 “(B) Any other locations where the institution of higher education
2 provides information about immigration or emergencies.
3 “(4) Notwithstanding subsection (3)(d) of this section, notice is not
4 required to be provided when a federal immigration authority has en-
5 tered campus for the purpose of accompanying a patient whom the
6 federal immigration authority has brought to the campus for the
7 purpose of receiving medical care or treatment.
8 “(5) For the purpose of ORS 30.265 (5), any officer, employee or
9 agent of an institution of higher education is immune from liability
10 for any claim for injury to or death of any person or injury to property
11 resulting from an act or omission made under this section if the act
12 or omission was reasonable and made in good faith.
13 “SECTION 3. No later than October 1, 2026, the Higher Education
14 Coordinating Commission shall submit to the interim committees of
15 the Legislative Assembly related to education a report that summa-
16 rizes for each institution of higher education the real property that
17 has been identified by the governing board of the institution of higher
18 education as a campus for the purpose of section 2 of this 2026 Act.
19 “SECTION 4. This 2026 Act takes effect on September 30, 2026.”.
